# Auto-commit after every task

After completing any meaningful change (file edits, new files, refactors, doc updates), immediately:

1. `git add` the relevant files
2. `git commit` with a concise message describing what changed
3. `git push` to the remote

Do this after each logical unit of work — don't batch multiple unrelated changes into one commit. If multiple files were changed as part of the same task, they go in one commit. If you do several separate tasks in a row, each gets its own commit + push.

Never skip the push step. The remote should always reflect the latest state.
